SERVICE(8)                                        System Manager's Manual                                        SERVICE(8)

NNAAMMEE
       service - run a System V init script

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       sseerrvviiccee _S_C_R_I_P_T _C_O_M_M_A_N_D [_O_P_T_I_O_N_S]

       sseerrvviiccee ----ssttaattuuss--aallll

       sseerrvviiccee ----hheellpp | --hh | ----vveerrssiioonn

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       sseerrvviiccee  runs a System V init script or systemd unit in as predictable an environment as possible, removing most en‚Äê
       vironment variables and with the current working directory set to //.

       The _S_C_R_I_P_T parameter specifies a System V init script, located in _/_e_t_c_/_i_n_i_t_._d_/_S_C_R_I_P_T, or the name of a systemd unit.
       The  existence  of a systemd unit of the same name as a script in //eettcc//iinniitt..dd will cause the unit to take precedence
       over the init.d script.  The supported values of _C_O_M_M_A_N_D depend on the invoked script. sseerrvviiccee passes  _C_O_M_M_A_N_D   and
       _O_P_T_I_O_N_S  to  the  init  script  unmodified. For systemd units, start, stop, status, and reload are passed through to
       their systemctl/initctl equivalents.

       All scripts should support at least the ssttaarrtt and ssttoopp commands.  As a special case, if _C_O_M_M_A_N_D  is  ----ffuullll--rreessttaarrtt,
       the script is run twice, first with the ssttoopp command, then with the ssttaarrtt command. Note, that unlike uuppddaattee--rrcc..dd(8),
       sseerrvviiccee does not check //uussrr//ssbbiinn//ppoolliiccyy--rrcc..dd.

       sseerrvviiccee ----ssttaattuuss--aallll runs all init scripts, in alphabetical order, with the ssttaattuuss command. The status is [ + ]  for
       running  services,  [  -  ]  for stopped services and [ ? ] for services without a ssttaattuuss command.  This option only
       calls status for sysvinit jobs.

EEXXIITT CCOODDEESS
       sseerrvviiccee calls the init script and returns the status returned by it.

FFIILLEESS
       //eettcc//iinniitt..dd
              The directory containing System V init scripts.

       //{{lliibb,,rruunn,,eettcc}}//ssyysstteemmdd//ssyysstteemm
              The directories containing systemd units.

EENNVVIIRROONNMMEENNTT
       LLAANNGG,, LLAANNGGUUAAGGEE,, LLCC__CCTTYYPPEE,, LLCC__NNUUMMEERRIICC,, LLCC__TTIIMMEE,, LLCC__CCOOLLLLAATTEE,, LLCC__MMOONNEETTAARRYY,, LLCC__MMEESSSSAAGGEESS,, LLCC__PPAAPPEERR,, LLCC__NNAAMMEE,,  LLCC__AADDDDRREESSSS,,
       LLCC__TTEELLEEPPHHOONNEE,, LLCC__MMEEAASSUURREEMMEENNTT,, LLCC__IIDDEENNTTIIFFIICCAATTIIOONN,, LLCC__AALLLL,, TTEERRMM,, PPAATTHH
              The only environment variables passed to the init scripts.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       _/_e_t_c_/_i_n_i_t_._d_/_s_k_e_l_e_t_o_n
